# Presentation Layer Rules

## Description
Shared rules for every file under `presentation/`. This rule keeps only cross-cutting presentation standards and defers folder-specific details to the dedicated presentation rules.

## Responsibilities
- Localize all user-visible text with `context.l10n`.
- Use project context extensions such as `context.l10n`, `context.colorScheme`, and `context.assets`.
- Never force-unwrap nullable values with `!` without an explicit guard.
- Keep presentation code inside the presentation layer and depend on domain abstractions only when needed.
- Treat form input as BLoC state, not controller-owned state.
- Follow the specific rule file for the current folder:
- `presentation-bloc.mdc` for `presentation/bloc/`
- `presentation-screens.mdc` for `presentation/screens/`
- `presentation-widgets.mdc` for `presentation/widgets/`
- Optional `presentation/theme/` (or similar) for app-wide presentation helpers scoped to the feature, e.g. `InheritedWidget` / theme bridges (`user_config` uses `app_theme_scope.dart`)
- `presentation-components.mdc` for shared presentation primitives and failure UI
- `core.mdc` for shared context extension conventions

## Green Flags
- User-visible text comes from `context.l10n`.
- Colors and assets come from `context.colorScheme` and `context.assets`.
- Nullable values are checked before use.
- Presentation files depend on domain abstractions instead of data-layer details.
- Form fields read from BLoC state instead of controller-owned state.
- Folder-specific concerns are handled by the matching presentation rule file instead of being duplicated here.

## Red Flags
- Hardcoded user-visible text, colors, asset paths, or other mutable design values.
- Force unwrapping nullable values with `!` without an explicit guard.
- Importing from a `data/` layer or another feature's `presentation/` layer.
- Using `TextEditingController` as the source of truth for feature form state.
- Duplicating detailed screen, widget, bloc, or component rules in this umbrella rule.
